<TITLE> India will weather global mkt turmoil: Pawan Kumar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Oct 20 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India will get through the global financial crisis because the government has taken timely steps to ward off the market turmoil on the domestic economy, the junior finance minister said on Monday. Indian authorities have taken several steps to ease a cash squeeze in the financial system, including cutting the reserve requirements of banks. "The global financial crisis is affecting the developing countries and India will be affected to some extent," junior finance minister Pawan Kumar Bansal said in a speech. "But we will be largely in a comfortable position to weather the storm as we have taken appropriate and timely action." He said containing inflation and maintaining a high pace of growth would be a major challenge during the financial turmoil
